children.text:
Siboney, I love you;
I am dying for your love.
Siboney, on your lips
honey placed its sweetness.
Come here, for I love you,
and you are every treasure to me.
Siboney, to the lull of your soul I think of you.
Siboney of my dreams, if you do not hear
the lament of my voice,
Siboney, if you do not come, I will die of love.
Siboney of my dreams, I wait for you
with longing in my caney;
Siboney, if you do not come, I will die of love.
Hear the echo of my crystal song
it does not vanish in the rough wilderness.
